title: UE unknown
description: When using the import process some of the projects (especially one I just created by opening up Unreal and creating a blank project with UE 5.6.1, blank56) are shjowing up as UE unknown.

title: Support version picking for creating projects
description: Like the import asset flow, it will need to download a version of the asset, provide the user with a dropdown on the version they wish to create the project with, then that version will be passed on to the download asset flow.

title: Import warning - unknown project version
description: When importing any asset now, the warning box shows up warning the user they are importing an asset into an unknown version. This was intended when importing a 5.6 asset into anything lower, such as 5.5, 4.X etc.

title: Finish setting up the question mark
description: Currently you either cannot click the question mark because it opens the unreal project or I miss clicked, but the long press option is still there. Instead, create a hover animation when hovering over the question mark, make it bigger so it's easier to press.

description: Somehow in Epic Asset Manager it displays all the images. Is this from the API or web scraping? Could we web scrape to get the images?
